   <text:p text:style-name="Horizontal_20_Line"/>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:soft-page-break/><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis">3. Results</text:span></text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">All major functionalities performed as expected:</text:p>
   <text:list xml:id="list1060284348" text:style-name="L24">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P48">Accurate calculation of module and degree scores </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P48">Proper classification boundaries applied </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P47">CLI handled invalid inputs gracefully </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
   </text:list>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_3" text:outline-level="3"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis">Issues Found &amp; Fixes</text:span></text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis">Issue 1: Missing Database Table</text:span></text:p>
   <text:list xml:id="list2725021796" text:style-name="L25">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P50">Error: <text:span text:style-name="Source_20_Text">no such table: students</text:span> </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P49">Fix: Corrected table name to <text:span text:style-name="Source_20_Text">StudentEnrolment</text:span> </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
   </text:list>
   <text:p text:style-name="Horizontal_20_Line"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis">Issue 2: Null Marks Handling</text:span></text:p>
   <text:list xml:id="list2017839202" text:style-name="L26">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P52">Problem: Null values caused incorrect calculations </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P51">Fix: Added checks: </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
   </text:list>
   <text:section text:style-name="Sect1" text:name="Section3">
    <text:p text:style-name="Preformatted_20_Text"><text:bookmark text:name="code-block-viewer2"/>if (a.getAwardedMarks() == null) return 0.0;</text:p>
   </text:section>
   <text:p text:style-name="Horizontal_20_Line"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis">Issue 3: Performance Inefficiency</text:span></text:p>
   <text:list xml:id="list961140259" text:style-name="L27">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P54">Problem: Recalculating module scores repeatedly </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P53">Fix: Introduced caching (<text:span text:style-name="Source_20_Text">cachedScore</text:span>) </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
   </text:list>
   <text:p text:style-name="Horizontal_20_Line"/>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis">Issue 4: Poor CLI Usability</text:span></text:p>
   <text:list xml:id="list1659015899" text:style-name="L28">
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P56">Problem: Users didn’t know valid module ranges </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
    <text:list-item>
     <text:p text:style-name="P55">Fix: Displayed ranges grouped by level before input </text:p>
    </text:list-item>
   </text:list>
   <text:p text:style-name="Horizontal_20_Line"/>
   <text:h text:style-name="Heading_20_2" text:outline-level="2"><text:span text:style-name="Strong_20_Emphasis">Conclusion</text:span></text:h>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">The SGC application demonstrates strong use of object-oriented design principles and provides a robust CLI for interacting with academic data. The system is efficient, extensible, and user-friendly, with clear separation of concerns between data handling, business logic, and user interaction.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body">Testing confirmed that the system behaves correctly under both valid and invalid inputs, and improvements were made to enhance performance and usability.</text:p>
   <text:p text:style-name="Text_20_body"/>
  </office:text>
 </office:body>
</office:document>